text.tspan: I choose to love my Lord
Comfort in Trials — By the Lord’s Love
When I come face to face with temptations,
It seems that I still haven’t yet learned.
So powerless my strength is to resist.
All I can do then is turn…
But even then, the guilt comes to haunt me:
My body’s full of weakness and sin.
Yet His word says, “new heart” He’s given me.
So I by faith say within…
Although I’ve failed, I know He still loves me.
He’s gaining me each step of the way.
His heart of love towards me shall never change.
Oh, how my heart burns to say…
I choose to love You, Lord,
With all my heart, with all my might!
